This is a trivial demonstration of using Python to generate the contents of a field. It is extremely limited. It grabs the default vernacular alternative of the citation form of every entry, runs it through a Python script that you supply, and then places the output in a different writing system alternative of the citation form. It is currently implemented in a very inefficient way; it actually runs the Python script once for every entry in the database. This utility will run the Python script found at (your FieldWorks install directory)\Language Explorer\UserScripts\TransduceCitationForms.py (the supplied sample script will add a Spanish alternative consisting of the default alternative, but with the case of each letter swapped.) Python must be part of your 'PATH' system variable.

Selected scripture sections are included in your text corpus and are available for interlinearization. Each section becomes a separate text.
If you clear a check box for a section it is no longer included as a text, however its words remain in the list of wordforms and any examples that reference it remain in the Lexicon area. If you include that section again, the interlinearization is remembered. You will need to refresh the window (F5) to see recent edits in the section. Check boxes with a gray check mark indicate that not all subordinate sections are currently selected.
You cannot edit any scripture in Language Explorer. (There is no additional help for this feature.)

当选的经文段已被加入文本素材，可以隔行对照化。每一段将成为分开的文本。
如你取消一段的核取项，它将不包括在文本里，但词还在词形列表里，所指的例子也在词库域里。如你重新勾选这段的核取项，已做的隔行对照化还在。如要看最近的编辑，你需要刷新窗口(F5)。变灰的核取项表示其中下级段没被勾选。
你不能在关于语言浏览器里任何经文。 (没有更多的帮助)。
